transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: My name is Robert, and I am a, I guess a member of ScoreBlue or whatever, but I had ordered some generic Viagra the other day, and I hit the wrong button, and I misordered what I wanted to, and I want to cancel that order, and I wanted to reorder something different.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I could pull up your account and see what you ordered, what's your last name and the zip code?

Speaker 2: Last name is Austin, and it's spelled A-A-S as in Sam, E-N, and the zip code is 55330.

Speaker 1: All right, let's pull that up here, and you made an order, when was it you said, yesterday?

Speaker 2: Yesterday or the day before.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay, wait a moment, let me see what's going on.

Speaker 2: And I tried getting a hold of you all day yesterday, and I couldn't get a hold of anybody, it's times that I could call.

Speaker 1: Oh, yeah, no worries, no worries.

Speaker 2: Okay, so were you trying to get the 40 pills of Viagra for?

Speaker 1: No, if you take a look at my, what's that?

Speaker 2: Yeah, because you have 50 pills for 263, that's the standard pricing for that.

Speaker 1: Other than that, yeah, let me see.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's the one that I don't, that's the one I don't want.

Speaker 1: Yeah, which one did you want?

Speaker 2: Okay, if you look at my prescriptions, can you pull that up?

Speaker 1: Previous order in November for a one-time only deal, you got it for 120 pills for one of our promotional pricings that they do for one-time orders, for first-time orders.

Speaker 2: That wasn't my first time, I look at my prescriptions, I've ordered tons of them.

Speaker 1: You made multiple accounts there, that's the problem.

Speaker 2: Basically, you have another account that you made, that you had orders on, and then you made a brand new account, which kind of tricked the system into thinking you had, there was a new account.

Speaker 1: You weren't supposed to get that deal to begin with, but you were able to, I guess, trick the system in that way, because you made another profile.

Speaker 2: Ah, okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so you weren't supposed to get that deal to start with, but I could cancel that out.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, I definitely do not want the 50 pills for $263.

Speaker 1: Yes, I could cancel that out, but the only other offer we have is 40 pills for $163, and that would be the only other offer.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that would be, and there's no promo codes that I could use?

Speaker 1: No, no, because you only get discounts for your first-time orders.
